<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-1420] Nonblocking and HsHa server should make sure to close all their socket connections when the selector exits</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-1420</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The way it currently works, if the server is commanded to stop, then clients will be left hanging, waiting for IO that will never complete. We should make sure that we clean up any open sockets on our way out of the selector.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12530134">THRIFT-1420</key>
            <summary>Nonblocking and HsHa server should make sure to close all their socket connections when the selector exits</summary>
